bilingual.source: We went to see a musical last night.

bilingual.source: She dreams of becoming a musical actress.

bilingual.source: The songs in this musical are very catchy.

bilingual.source: We plan to see a musical on Broadway.
bilingual.target: 我们计划去百老汇看一场音乐剧。

bilingual.source: I watched a musical at the theater last night.
bilingual.target: 我昨晚在剧院看了一场音乐剧。

bilingual.source: He composed several new tunes for the musical.
bilingual.target: 他为这部音乐剧创作了几首新的曲调。

bilingual.source: They plan to restage the musical next summer.
bilingual.target: 他们计划明年夏天重新上演这部音乐剧。

bilingual.source: The new musical on Broadway has received rave reviews.
bilingual.target: 百老汇上的新音乐剧获得了好评如潮。

bilingual.source: They are rehearsing for the school musical this weekend.
bilingual.target: 他们这个周末在为学校的音乐剧排练。

yingyinNormal.en: It's all part of their plan to ruin our musical.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他们计划毁掉我们的音乐剧。

yingyinNormal.en: You missed free period workout yesterday to audition for a heinous musical.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你昨天为了音乐剧试镜没参加自由时间的练习。

yingyinNormal.en: You are so dedicated. Just like me. I hope you come watch me in the musical. Promise? Toodles. Toodles.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你真是用心，跟我一样。我希望你能来看我的音乐剧，答应我？再见。再见。

yingyinNormal.en: Life isn't some cartoon musical where you sing a little song, and your insipid dreams magically come true! So let it go.
yingyinNormal.zh: 生活不是卡通音乐剧，只要唱唱跳跳的，然后无聊的梦就奇迹般地成真了！放手吧。

yingyinNormal.en: It's full of musical instruments. They are a bit old and dusty.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这里面都是演奏用的乐器。灰尘好像有点多。

yingyinNormal.en: So have you decided on a band for the wedding? Because, you know, I'm kinda musical.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你决定婚礼用的乐团了吗？因为我也是音乐家。

yingyinNormal.en: It's like musical chairs. The music stopped and they were the last two left standing.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这就好比抢椅子游戏，音乐停了，只有他俩没抢到。

yingyinNormal.en: Let's get this party started. Who wants to play "Musical statues"? Yeah. This is what you do.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们的派对马上就要开始了。谁想玩音乐雕像的游戏。我。我们要这样来玩。

yingyinNormal.en: What am I going to do? Well, why don't you send her a musical bug, oh, no you already did that.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我该怎么办？何不送她一个音乐金龟？不，你已经送过了。

yingyinNormal.en: Now the UN secretary general Ban Ki-moon said: There are no languages required in a musical world.
yingyinNormal.zh: 联合国秘书长潘基文说，在音乐的世界里，不需要语言。

yingyinNormal.en: But one day, before the opening night of our school's annual musical, he walked up to me and holding a letter.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但是有一天在我们学校年度音乐会的前一个晚上，他走到我面前，拿着一封信。

yingyinNormal.en: He showed up in the middle of the night with his bongos. I foolishly thought it was some sort of musical booty call.
yingyinNormal.zh: 昨晚半夜他带着小手鼓出现，我错误以为这是某种音乐求欢方式。

yingyinNormal.en: Unbelievable. That's what I thought, but then Andy and I did some digging. It turns out pigs are crazy musical. Good ol' Andy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不可思议。我开始也这么想，不过我们后来做了调查，原来猪超有音乐天赋。又是安迪。

yingyinNormal.en: Mummy, "Musical Statues" is over. Lovely. Now it's time for "Pass the Parcel". Yeah. When the music plays, pass the parcel round.
yingyinNormal.zh: 妈妈，音乐雕塑的游戏结束了。非常好，现在来玩接鼓传花的游戏吧。好的。当音乐响起来的时候，就要把这个包裹传给别人。

yingyinNormal.en: The trick is to synchronize a kick that can penetrate all three levels. We could use a musical countdown to synchronize the different kicks.
yingyinNormal.zh: 实施堕醒同步化三层梦空间，可用音乐来倒计不同层次的堕醒。

yingyinNormal.en: What's baffling me is what you could've possibly put on the list. Hair too golden? Laugh too musical? World too much a better place for her mere presence in it"?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不解的是你能列出什么问题，秀发太金黄？笑声太动听？她的出现让世界更美好？
